pokedex_entry: A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. The plant sprouts and grows with this POKÃ©MON.
When the bulb on its back grows large, it appears to lose the ability to stand on its hind legs.
The plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.
Obviously prefers hot places. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.
When it swings its burning tail, it elevates the temperature to unbearably high levels.
Spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. Known to cause forest fires unintentionally.
After birth, its back swells and hardens into a shell. Powerfully sprays foam from its mouth.
Often hides in water to stalk unwary prey. For swimming fast, it moves its ears to maintain balance.
A brutal POKÃ©MON with pressurized water jets on its shell. They are used for high speed tackles.

This POKÃ©MON is vulnerable to attack while its shell is soft, exposing its weak and tender body.
In battle, it flaps its wings at high speed to release highly toxic dust into the air.
Often found in forests, eating leaves. It has a sharp venomous stinger on its head.
Almost incapable of moving, this POKÃ©MON can only harden its shell to protect itself from predators.
It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.
A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.
Very protective of its sprawling territorial area, this POKÃ©MON will fiercely peck at any intruder.
When hunting, it skims the surface of water at high speed to pick off unwary prey such as MAGIKARP.

With its huge and magnificent wings, it can keep aloft without ever having to land for rest.
Moves silently and stealthily. Eats the eggs of birds, such as PIDGEY and SPEAROW, whole.
It is rumored that the ferocious warning markings on its belly differ from area to area.
When several of these POKÃ©MON gather, their electricity could build and cause lightning storms.
Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself from its own high-voltage power.
Burrows deep underground in arid locations far from water. It only emerges to hunt for food.
Curls up into a spiny ball when threatened. It can roll while curled up to attack or escape.
Although small, its venomous barbs render this POKÃ©MON dangerous. The female has smaller horns.
The female's horn develops slowly. Prefers physical attacks such as clawing and biting.
Its hard scales provide strong protection. It uses its hefty bulk to execute powerful moves.
Stiffens its ears to sense danger. The larger its horns, the more powerful its secreted venom.

Its magical and cute appeal has many admirers. It is rare and found only in certain areas.
A timid fairy POKÃ©MON that is rarely seen. It will run and hide the moment it senses people.
At the time of birth, it has just one tail. The tail splits from its tip as it grows older.
Very smart and very vengeful. Grabbing one of its many tails could result in a 1000-year curse.
When its huge eyes light up, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.
The body is soft and rubbery. When angered, it will suck in air and inflate itself to an enormous size.

The fluid that oozes from its mouth isn't drool. It is a nectar that is used to attract prey.
It has the worldâs largest petals. With every step, the petals shake out heavy clouds of toxic pollen.
Burrows to suck tree roots. The mushrooms on its back grow by drawÂ­ ing nutrients from the bug host.
A host-parasite pair in which the parasite mushroom has taken over the host bug. Prefers damp places.
Lives in the shadows of tall trees where it eats insects. It is attracted by light at night.
The dustlike scales covering its wings are color-coded to indicate the kinds of poison it has.

Although its fur has many admirers, it is tough to raise as a pet because of its fickle meanness.
While lulling its enemies with its vacant look, this wily POKÃ©MON will use psychokinetic powers.
Often seen swimÂ­ ming elegantly by lake shores. It is often mistaken for the Japanese monster, Kappa.
Extremely quick to anger. It could be docile one moment then thrashing away the next instant.
Always furious and tenacious to boot. It will not abandon chasing its quarry until it is caught.
Very protective of its territory. It will bark and bite to repel intruders from its space.
A POKÃ©MON that has been admired since the past for its beauty. It runs agilely as if on wings.
Its newly grown legs prevent it from running. It appears to prefer swimming than trying to stand.
Capable of living in or out of water. When out of water, it sweats to keep its body slimy.
An adept swimmer at both the front crawl and breast stroke. Easily overtakes the best human swimmers.
Using its ability to read minds, it will identify impending danger and TELEPORT to safety.
It emits special alpha waves from its body that induce headaches just by being close by.
Its brain can outÂ­ perform a superÂ­ computer. Its intelligence quotient is said to be 5,000.

Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power save belt to be able to regulate its motions.
Using its heavy muscles, it throws powerful punches that can send the victim clear over the horizon.
A carnivorous POKÃ©MON that traps and eats bugs. It uses its root feet to soak up needed moisture.
It spits out POISONPOWDER to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of ACID.

Drifts in shallow seas. Anglers who hook them by accident are often punished by its stinging acid.
The tentacles are normally kept short. On hunts, they are extended to ensnare and immobilize prey.
Found in fields and mountains. Mistaking them for boulders, people often step or trip on them.

Uses anti-gravity to stay suspended. Appears without warning and uses THUNDER WAVE and similar moves.
Formed by several MAGNEMITEs linked together. They frequently appear when sunspots flare up.
The sprig of green onions it holds is its weapon. It is used much like a metal sword.
A bird that makes up for its poor flying with its fast foot speed. Leaves giant footprints.
The protruding horn on its head is very hard. It is used for bashing through thick ice.
Stores thermal energy in its body. Swims at a steady 8 knots even in intensely cold waters.
Appears in filthy areas. Thrives by sucking up polluted sludge that is pumped out of factories.
Thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.
Its hard shell repels any kind of attack. It is vulnerable only when its shell is open.
When attacked, it launches its horns in quick volleys. Its innards have never been seen.
Almost invisible, this gaseous POKÃ©MON cloaks the target and puts it to sleep without notice.
Because of its ability to slip through block walls, it is said to be from anÂ­ other dimension.
Under a full moon, this POKÃ©MON likes to mimic the shadows of people and laugh at their fright.
As it grows, the stone portions of its body harden to become similar to a diamond, but colored black.
Puts enemies to sleep then eats their dreams. Occasionally gets sick from eating bad dreams.
When it locks eyes with an enemy, it will use a mix of PSI moves such as HYPNOSIS and CONFUSION.
Its pincers are not only powerful weapons, they are used for balance when walking sideways.
The large pincer has 10000 hp of crushing power. However, its huge size makes it unwieldy to use.
Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a POKÃ© BALL, they have zapped many people.
It stores electric energy under very high pressure. It often explodes with little or no provocation.
Often mistaken for eggs. When disturbed, they quickly gather and attack in swarms.
Legend has it that on rare occasions, one of its heads will drop off and continue on as an EXEGGCUTE.
Because it never removes its skull helmet, no one has ever seen this POKÃ©MON's real face.

When in a hurry, its legs lengthen progressively. It runs smoothly with extra long, loping strides.
While apparently doing nothing, it fires punches in lightning fast volleys that are impossible to see.
Its tongue can be extended like a chameleon's. It leaves a tingling sensation when it licks enemies.
Because it stores several kinds of toxic gases in its body, it is prone to exploding without warning.
Where two kinds of poison gases meet, 2 KOFFINGs can fuse into a WEEZING over many years.
A POKÃ©MON with a one-track mind. Once it charges,  it won't stop running until it falls asleep.
Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees.
A rare and elusive POKÃ©MON that is said to bring happiness to those who manage to get it.
The whole body is swathed with wide vines that are similar to seaÂ­ weed. Its vines shake as it walks.
The infant rarely ventures out of its mother's protective pouch until it is 3 years old.
Known to shoot down flying bugs with precision blasts of ink from the surface of the water.
Capable of swimÂ­ ming backwards by rapidly flapping its wing-like pectoral fins and stout tail.
Its tail fin billows like an elegant ballroom dress, giving it the nickname of the Water Queen.
In the autumn spawning season, they can be seen swimming powerfully up rivers and creeks.
If its body is torn, it can grow back if the red core remains. The core flashes at midnight.
Its central core glows with the seven colors of the rainbow. Some people value the core as a gem.
If interrupted while it is miming, it will slap around the offender with its broad hands.
With ninja-like agility and speed, it can create the illusion that there is more than one.
It seductively wiggles its hips as it walks. It can cause people to dance in unison with it.
Normally found near power plants, they can wander away and cause major blackouts in cities.
Its body always burns with an orange glow that enables it to hide perfectly among flames.
If it fails to crush the victim in its pincers, it will swing it around and toss it hard.
When it targets an enemy, it charges furiously while whipping its body with its long tails.
In the distant past, it was somewhat stronger than the horribly weak descendants that exist today.
Once it begins to rampage, a GYARADOS will burn everything down, even in a harsh storm.
A POKÃ©MON that has been overÂ­ hunted almost to extinction. It can ferry people across the water.
Capable of copying an enemy's genetic code to instantly transform itself into a duplicate of the enemy.
Its genetic code is irregular. It may mutate if it is exposed to radiation from element STONEs.
Lives close to water. Its long tail is ridged with a fin which is often mistaken for a mermaid's.
It accumulates negative ions in the atmosphere to blast out 10000- volt lightning bolts.
When storing thermal energy in its body, its temperature could soar to over 1600 degrees.
A POKÃ©MON that consists entirely of programming code. Capable of moving freely in cyberspace.
Although long extinct, in rare cases, it can be genetically resurrected from fossils.
A prehistoric POKÃ©MON that died out when its heavy shell made it impossible to catch prey.
A POKÃ©MON that was resurrected from a fossil found in what was once the ocean floor eons ago.
Ã un perfetto nuotatore. Taglia la preda con le sue falci e ne succhia il sangue.
A PokÃ©mon that roamed the skies in the dinosaur era. Its teeth are like saw blades.
Very lazy. Just eats and sleeps. As its rotund bulk builds, it becomes steadily more slothful.
A legendary bird POKÃ©MON that is said to appear to doomed people who are lost in icy mountains.
Known as the legendary bird of fire. Every flap of its wings creates a dazzling flash of flames.
Long considered a mythical POKÃ©MON until recently when a small colony was found living underwater.

An extremely rarely seen marine POKÃ©MON. Its intelligence is said to match that of humans.
It was created by a scientist after years of horrific gene splicing and DNA engineering experiments.
So rare that it is still said to be a mirage by many experts. Only a few people have seen it worldwide.
A sweet aroma gently wafts from the leaf on its head. It is docile and loves to soak up the sun's rays.
The scent of spices comes from around its neck. Somehow, sniffing it makes you want to fight.
The aroma that rises from its petals contains a substance that calms aggressive feelings.
It has a timid nature. If it is startled, the flames on its back burn more vigorously.
Be careful if it turns its back during battle. It means that it will attack with the fire on its back.
If its rage peaks, it becomes so hot that anything that touches it will instantly go up in flames.
Its well-developed jaws are powerful and capable of crushing anything. Even its trainer must be careful.
If it loses a fang, a new one grows back in its place. There are always 48 fangs lining its mouth.
When it bites with its massive and powerful jaws, it shakes its head and savagely tears its victim up.
A very cautious POKÃ©MON, it raises itself up using its tail to get a better view of its surroundings.
It makes a nest to suit its long and skinny body. The nest is impossible for other POKÃ©MON to enter.
It always stands on one foot. It changes feet so fast, the movement can rarely be seen.
Its eyes are specially adapted. They concentrate even faint light and enable it to see in the dark.
It is very timid. It will be afraid to move if it is alone. But it will be active if it is in a group.
When the stars flicker in the night sky, it flutters about, scattering a glowing powder.
It lies still in the same pose for days in its web, waiting for its unsuspecting prey to wander close.

Chinchou blink their shining antennae at one another to claim their respective turf.
The light it emits is so bright that it can illuminate the sea's surface from a depth of over three miles.
It is not yet skilled at storing electricity. It may send out a jolt if amused or startled.
Because of its unusual, star-like silhouette, people believe that it came here on a meteor.
It has a very soft body. If it starts to roll, it will bounce all over and be impossible to stop.
The shell seems to be filled with joy. It is said that it will share good luck when treated kindly.
They say that it will appear before kindhearted, carÂ­ ing people and shower them with happiness.
Because its wings aren't yet fully grown, it has to hop to get around. It is always starÂ­ ing at something.
They say that it stays still and quiet because it is seeing both the past and future at the same time.
If static elecÂ­ tricity builds in its body, its fleece doubles in volume. Touching it will shock you.

It lives in water virtually all day long. Its body color and pattern act as camouflage that makes it tough for enemies to spot in water.
Although it always pretends to be a tree, its composiÂ­ tion appears to be closer to a rock than a plant.
If POLIWAG and POLIWHIRL hear its echoing cry, they respond by gatherÂ­ ing from far and wide.
To keep from being blown away by the wind, they gather in clusters. They do enjoy gentle breezes, though.
The bloom on top of its head opens and closes as the temperature flucÂ­ tuates up and down.
Once it catches the wind, it deftÂ­ ly controls its cotton-puff spores to float, even around the world.
Sa queue est aussi agile que ses mains. Il vit en haut des grands arbres.

It converts sunÂ­ light into energy. In the darkness after sunset, it closes its petals and becomes still.
If it flaps its wings really fast, it can generate shock waves that will shatter winÂ­ dows in the area.
This POKÃ©MON lives in cold water. It will leave the water to search for food when it gets cold outside.
This carefree POKÃ©MON has an easy-going nature. While swimming, it always bumps into boat hulls.
It uses the fine hair that covers its body to sense air currents and predict its eneÂ­ my's actions.
When agitated, this POKÃ©MON proÂ­ tects itself by spraying poisonous sweat from its pores.
Feared and loathed by many, it is believed to bring misfortune to all those who see it at night.
It has incredible intellect and inÂ­ tuition. Whatever the situation, it remains calm and collected.
It likes playing mischievous tricks such as screaming and wailing to startle people at night.
Their shapes look like hieroglyphs on ancient tabÂ­ lets. It is said that the two are somehow related.
Odia la luz y las sacudidas. Si le atacan, infla su cuerpo para aumentar su contraataque.
Its tail has a small brain of its own. Beware! If you get close, it may react to your scent and bite.
It likes to make its shell thicker by adding layers of tree bark. The additional weight doesn't bother it.
Its entire body is shielded by a steel-hard shell. What lurks inside the armor is a total mystery.
When spotted, this POKÃ©MON escapes backward by furiÂ­ ously boring into the ground with its tail.
It flies straight at its target's face then clamps down on the starÂ­ tled victim to inject poison.
It is thought its body transformed as a result of iron accumulating internally from swallowing soil.
Although it looks frightening, it is actually kind and affectionate. It is very popular among women.
It is actually timid and easily spooked. If atÂ­ tacked, it flails about to fend off its attacker.
To fire its poison spikes, it must inflate its body by drinking over 2.6 gallons of water all at once.
It has a steel-hard body. It intimidates foes by upraising its eye-patterned pincers.
The BERRIES it stores in its vase-like shell decompose and become a gooey liquid.
It is usually docile, but if it is disturbed while sipping honey, it chases off the intruder with its horn.

It rubs its snout on the ground to find and dig up food. It sometimes discovers hot springs.

It uses different kinds of cries for communicating with others of its kind and for pursuing its prey.
If you are burned by the flames it shoots from its mouth, the pain will never go away.
It is said that it usually hides in underwater caves. It can create whirlpools by yawning.
It swings its long snout around playÂ­ fully, but because it is so strong, that can be danÂ­ gerous.
It has sharp, hard tusks and a rugged hide. Its TACKLE is strong enough to knock down a house.
This upgraded version of PORYGON is designed for space exploration. It can't fly, though.
The curved antlers subtly change the flow of air to create a strange space where realÂ­ ity is distorted.
A special fluid oozes from the tip of its tail. It paints the fluid everywhere to mark its territory.
It is always bursting with enÂ­ ergy. To make itÂ­ self stronger, it keeps on fighting even if it loses.
If you become enchanted by its smooth, elegant, dance-like kicks, you may get drilled hard.
Its lips are the most sensitive parts on its body. It always uses its lips first to examine things.

Si tiene crÃ­as, la leche que produce contiene muchos mÃ¡s nutrientes de lo normal.
Anyone who takes even one bite of BLISSEY's egg beÂ­ comes unfailingly caring and pleasÂ­ ant to everyone.
The rain clouds it carries let it fire thunderbolts at will. They say that it descended with lightning.
Volcanoes erupt when it barks. UnÂ­ able to restrain its extreme power, it races headlong around the land.
It races around the world to purify fouled water. It dashes away with the north wind.
It feeds on soil. After it has eaten a large mountain, it will fall asleep so it can grow.
Its shell is as hard as sheet rock, and it is also very strong. Its THRASHING can topple a mountain.
Its body can't be harmed by any sort of attack, so it is very eager to make challenges against enemies.
It is said that it quietly spends its time deep at the bottom of the sea because its powers are too strong.
Legends claim this POKÃ©MON flies the world's skies conÂ­ tinuously on its magnificent seven- colored wings.
This POKÃ©MON wanÂ­ ders across time. Grass and trees flourish in the forests in which it has appeared.
TREECKO has small hooks on the bottom of its feet that enable it to scale vertical walls. This POKÃ©MON attacks by slamming foes with its thick tail.

The leaves growing on SCEPTILEâs body are very sharp edged. This POKÃ©MON is very agile - it leaps all over the branches of trees and jumps on its foe from above or behind.
TORCHIC sticks with its TRAINER, following behind with unsteady steps. This POKÃ©MON breathes fire of over 1,800 degrees F, including fireballs that leave the foe scorched black.
COMBUSKEN toughens up its legs and thighs by running through fields and mountains. This POKÃ©MONâs legs possess both speed and power, enabling it to dole out ten kicks in one second.
In battle, BLAZIKEN blows out intense flames from its wrists and attacks foes courageously. The stronger the foe, the more intensely this POKÃ©MONâs wrists burn.
The fin on MUDKIPâs head acts as highly sensitive radar. Using this fin to sense movements of water and air, this POKÃ©MON can determine what is taking place around it without using its eyes.
The surface of MARSHTOMPâs body is enveloped by a thin, sticky film that enables it to live on land. This POKÃ©MON plays in mud on beaches when the ocean tide is low.
SWAMPERT is very strong. It has enough power to easily drag a boulder weighing more than a ton. This POKÃ©MON also has powerful vision that lets it see even in murky water.
At first sight, POOCHYENA takes a bite at anything that moves. This POKÃ©MON chases after prey until the victim becomes exhausted. However, it may turn tail if the prey strikes back.
Les GrahyÃ¨na forment des meutes de dix qui excellent au travail de groupe pour capturer leurs proies.
ZIGZAGOON restlessly wanders everywhere at all times. This POKÃ©MON does so because it is very curious. It becomes interested in anything that it happens to see.
LINOONE always runs full speed and only in straight lines. If facing an obstacle, it makes a right-angle turn to evade it. This POKÃ©MON is very challenged by gently curving roads.
Le encanta comer hojas. Si le ataca un Starly, se defenderÃ¡ con sus pÃºas.
SILCOON tethers itself to a tree branch using silk to keep from falling. There,  this POKÃ©MON hangs quietly while it awaits evolution. It peers out of the silk cocoon through a small hole.
BEAUTIFLYâs favorite food is the sweet pollen of flowers. If you want to see this POKÃ©MON, just leave a potted flower by an open window. BEAUTIFLY is sure to come looking for pollen.

CASCOON makes its protective cocoon by wrapping its body entirely with a fine silk from its mouth. Once the silk goes around its body, it hardens. This POKÃ©MON prepares for its evolution inside the cocoon.
DUSTOX is instinctively drawn to light. Swarms of this POKÃ©MON are attracted by the bright lights of cities, where they wreak havoc by stripping the leaves off roadside trees for food.
It searches about for clean water. If it does not drink water for too long, the leaf on its head wilts.
It lives at the waterâs edge where it is sunny. It sleeps on a bed of water grass by day and becomes active at night.
LUDICOLO begins dancing as soon as it hears cheerful, festive music. This POKÃ©MON is said to appear when it hears the singing of children on hiking outings.
SEEDOT attaches itself to a tree branch using the top of its head. It sucks moisture from the tree while hanging off the branch. The more water it drinks, the glossier this POKÃ©MONâs body becomes.
NUZLEAF live in densely overgrown forests. They occasionally venture out of the forest to startle people. This POKÃ©MON dislikes having its long nose pinched.
It lives quietly in the deep forest. It is said to create chilly winter winds with the fans it holds.
TAILLOW courageously stands its ground against foes, however strong they may be. This gutsy POKÃ©MON will remain defiant even after a loss. On the other hand, it cries loudly if it becomes hungry.

SWELLOW flies high above our heads, making graceful arcs in the sky. This POKÃ©MON dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. The hapless prey is tightly grasped by SWELLOWâs clawed feet, preventing escape.
WINGULL has the habit of carrying prey and valuables in its beak and hiding them in all sorts of locations. This POKÃ©MON rides the winds and flies as if it were skating across the sky.
